<td width="50%"><b><a href="/wiki/List_of_historical_national_capitals" title="List of historical national capitals" class="mw-redirect">Capital</a></b></td>
<td width="50%"><small><a href="/wiki/Rome" title="Rome">Rome</a> was the sole political capital until AD 286<br />
Under the <a href="/wiki/Tetrarchy" title="Tetrarchy">Tetrarchy</a> there were several political centres, while Rome continued to be the nominal, cultural, and ideological capital of the entire empire.<br />
Under the rule of <a href="/wiki/Constantine_I" title="Constantine I">Constantine</a> the empire had two capitals, Rome and <a href="/wiki/Constantinople" title="Constantinople">Constantinople</a>.<br />
The western imperial court would be later relocated to <a href="/wiki/Ravenna" title="Ravenna">Ravenna</a>.</small></td>
</tr>
